  "suggestion": "Evolution is choosing beautiful but expensive organisms. Reduce physics overhead and increase resource efficiency to sustain life longer.; Efficiency is the critical bottleneck (0.241 vs. 0.5-0.74 for survival/beauty). Organisms are dying with depleted energy across all lifecycles (ages 230-407), indicating unsustainable energy expenditure. In particle physics simulations, efficiency depends on: (1) energy cost of movement (springStiffness, swimStrength, drag), (2) energy gain from resources (resourceAttraction, harvestThreshold), and (3) structural maintenance. The solution: reduce movement overhead via higher drag (less resistance) and lower spring stiffness, increase resource acquisition via higher resourceAttraction and energyConserve, and optimize active swimming only when beneficial.",
